      "flags": {},
      "order": 10,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "REALTIME DRAWING - quickstart\n\n1) Point the Checkpoint at a FAST few-step model. A PLAIN model\n   (v1-5-pruned, SDXL base, DreamShaper/Juggernaut with NO\n   LCM/Turbo/Lightning/Hyper in the name) will NOT work - it barely\n   denoises at 4 steps, so the output stays ~99% your drawing.\n   Recommended:\n   - SD1.5 zero-setup drop-in (works with THIS graph as-is):\n     DreamShaper8_LCM.safetensors  (HF: Lykon/dreamshaper-8-lcm)\n   - SDXL, best quality (10GB+ VRAM): sdxl_lightning_4step.safetensors\n     (HF: ByteDance/SDXL-Lightning) - then set the KSampler to\n     sampler=euler, scheduler=sgm_uniform, CFG 1.0, and do NOT add an\n     LCM LoRA (Lightning is already few-step).\n\n2) In Photoshop: open the ComfyUI Bridge panel, Start Live, and draw.\n\n3) The PROMPT and CREATIVITY controls are in the 'ComfyUI Preview'\n   panel (Plugins > ComfyUI Bridge > ComfyUI Preview), under the image:\n   - PROMPT box drives the 'Photoshop Live Prompt' node here.\n   - CREATIVITY slider drives the 'Photoshop Live Creativity' node,\n     which sets this KSampler's denoise. Low = hug your drawing,\n     high = reinterpret it. That is the fix for 'looks like my drawing':\n     effective work ~= steps x denoise, so at 4 steps keep it high\n     enough (the slider maps to denoise 0.40-0.85 by default).\n\nYou never have to edit this graph to change the prompt or adherence -\ndo it from the Photoshop panel."
      ],
      "title": "READ ME \u2014 realtime drawing quickstart",
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
